# No Backup Artifacts in the Shipped App

The deployed Vercel build must contain **only** the assets actually imported
or served by the live demo. Prior/experimental versions are preserved as
untracked, gitignored sidecars on the maintainer's machine — never in source
control, never in `dist/`.

## Naming convention

Anything intentionally kept as a local-only reference uses these patterns
(all covered by `.gitignore`):

- `*.backup.*` — e.g. `dhyh-tier3.backup.json`, `dhyh-cmp.backup.mp4`
- `_backups/` — ad-hoc folder for larger snapshots
- `_Temp/` and `_Temp_Ads/` — reserved for in-flight asset moves only

## Rules for the agent

- **Never** `git add` a file matching `*.backup.*`, `_backups/**`, or
  `_Temp*/**`. Warn the user and skip it, even when they ask for `git add .`.
- When replacing a committed asset (JSON, MP4, JPG), make the backup a
  `*.backup.*` sidecar in the same directory. Do not stage it.
- Media under `public/assets/` is copied verbatim into `dist/`. Treat every
  file there as a bandwidth cost on Vercel — confirm with the user before
  committing anything > 10 MB.
- `src/assets/data/*.json` is imported dynamically via `await import(...)`.
  Only the files that are referenced in `src/demo/dhyhScenes.ts` may live
  under `src/assets/data/` without the `.backup.json` suffix.

## Canonical asset map (live / deployed)

| Purpose | Deployed path |
|---|---|
| Tier 1 (Basic Scene) JSON | `src/assets/data/dhyh-tier1.json` |
| Tier 2 (Advanced Scene) JSON | `src/assets/data/dhyh-tier2.json` |
| Tier 3 (Exact Match) JSON | `src/assets/data/dhyh-tier3.json` |
| DHYH video (web-optimized) | `public/assets/video/dhyh-cmp.mp4` |
| Ad creatives | `public/assets/ads/SD-HD-Tools-*.mp4` |
| Product images | `public/assets/products/homedpt/*.jpg` |

Anything else in those directories — including files whose name contains
`backup`, `old`, `temp`, `_v2`, `-copy`, or a date stamp — is not shipped.
